            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EIsaac%20was%20a%20man%20whose%20life%20demonstrated%20the%20blessing%20of%20God.%20He%20was%20undoubtedly%20a%20tithing%20believer%20and%20a%20successful%20farmer%2C%20as%20were%20his%20father%20Abraham%20and%20son%20Jacob.%20Genesis%2026%3A12%20tells%20us%2C%20%22That%20year%20Isaac's%20crops%20were%20tremendous!%20He%20harvested%20a%20hundred%20times%20more%20grain%20than%20he%20planted%2C%20for%20the%20Lord%20blessed%20him.%22%20While%20others%20were%20perishing%20in%20the%20famine%2C%20Isaac%20sowed%20in%20the%20land%20and%20reaped%20a%20hundredfold%20return.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIt%20was%20Isaac's%20attitude%2C%20however%2C%20that%20brought%20the%20blessing%20of%20God.%20When%20he%20had%20dug%20a%20%22gushing%20spring%22%20(Genesis%2026%3A19)%2C%20the%20shepherds%20of%20Gerar%20came%20and%20stole%20it%20from%20him.%20Instead%20of%20quarreling%2C%20he%20moved%20on%20and%20%22dug%20another%20well%22%20(v.%2021).%20When%20that%20new%20well%20was%20stolen%2C%20%22he%20dug%20another%20well%22%20(v.%2022).%20Finally%20his%20well%20was%20not%20stolen%2C%20and%20the%20Lord%20said%20to%20him%2C%20%22Do%20not%20be%20afraid%2C%20for%20I%20am%20with%20you%20and%20will%20bless%20you%22%20(v.%2024).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EAttitudes%20of%20bitterness%2C%20anger%2C%20resentment%2C%20and%20strife%20will%20keep%20you%20from%20financial%20blessing.%20Dig%20another%20well%2C%20keep%20your%20heart%20right%2C%20and%20God%20will%20pour%20out%20even%20more%20blessings%20than%20before!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "Genesis.26:17-27:46",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3EGenesis%2026%3A17-27%3A46%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_17%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Isaac%20moved%20away%20to%20the%20Gerar%20Valley%2C%20where%20he%20set%20up%20their%20tents%20and%20settled%20down.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_18%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20reopened%20the%20wells%20his%20father%20had%20dug%2C%20which%20the%20Philistines%20had%20filled%20in%20after%20Abraham%26%23x2019%3Bs%20death.%20Isaac%20also%20restored%20the%20names%20Abraham%20had%20given%20them.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_19%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EIsaac%26%23x2019%3Bs%20servants%20also%20dug%20in%20the%20Gerar%20Valley%20and%20discovered%20a%20well%20of%20fresh%20water.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_20%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20then%20the%20shepherds%20from%20Gerar%20came%20and%20claimed%20the%20spring.%20%26%23x201C%3BThis%20is%20our%20water%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20they%20said%2C%20and%20they%20argued%20over%20it%20with%20Isaac%26%23x2019%3Bs%20herdsmen.%20So%20Isaac%20named%20the%20well%20Esek%20(which%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Bargument%26%23x201D%3B).%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_21%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3EIsaac%26%23x2019%3Bs%20men%20then%20dug%20another%20well%2C%20but%20again%20there%20was%20a%20dispute%20over%20it.%20So%20Isaac%20named%20it%20Sitnah%20(which%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Bhostility%26%23x201D%3B).%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_22%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EAbandoning%20that%20one%2C%20Isaac%20moved%20on%20and%20dug%20another%20well.%20This%20time%20there%20was%20no%20dispute%20over%20it%2C%20so%20Isaac%20named%20the%20place%20Rehoboth%20(which%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Bopen%20space%26%23x201D%3B)%2C%20for%20he%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BAt%20last%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20created%20enough%20space%20for%20us%20to%20prosper%20in%20this%20land.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_23%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EFrom%20there%20Isaac%20moved%20to%20Beersheba%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_24%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3Ewhere%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20appeared%20to%20him%20on%20the%20night%20of%20his%20arrival.%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20am%20the%20God%20of%20your%20father%2C%20Abraham%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20said.%20%26%23x201C%3BDo%20not%20be%20afraid%2C%20for%20I%20am%20with%20you%20and%20will%20bless%20you.%20I%20will%20multiply%20your%20descendants%2C%20and%20they%20will%20become%20a%20great%20nation.%20I%20will%20do%20this%20because%20of%20my%20promise%20to%20Abraham%2C%20my%20servant.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_25%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Isaac%20built%20an%20altar%20there%20and%20worshiped%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20He%20set%20up%20his%20camp%20at%20that%20place%2C%20and%20his%20servants%20dug%20another%20well.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_26%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EIsaac%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Covenant%20with%20Abimelech%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20day%20King%20Abimelech%20came%20from%20Gerar%20with%20his%20adviser%2C%20Ahuzzath%2C%20and%20also%20Phicol%2C%20his%20army%20commander.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_27%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20have%20you%20come%20here%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Isaac%20asked.%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20obviously%20hate%20me%2C%20since%20you%20kicked%20me%20off%20your%20land.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_28%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWe%20can%20plainly%20see%20that%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20with%20you.%20So%20we%20want%20to%20enter%20into%20a%20sworn%20treaty%20with%20you.%20Let%26%23x2019%3Bs%20make%20a%20covenant.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_29%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3ESwear%20that%20you%20will%20not%20harm%20us%2C%20just%20as%20we%20have%20never%20troubled%20you.%20We%20have%20always%20treated%20you%20well%2C%20and%20we%20sent%20you%20away%20from%20us%20in%20peace.%20And%20now%20look%20how%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20has%20blessed%20you!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_30%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2230%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Isaac%20prepared%20a%20covenant%20feast%20to%20celebrate%20the%20treaty%2C%20and%20they%20ate%20and%20drank%20together.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_31%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2231%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E31%3C%2Fspan%3EEarly%20the%20next%20morning%2C%20they%20each%20took%20a%20solemn%20oath%20not%20to%20interfere%20with%20each%20other.%20Then%20Isaac%20sent%20them%20home%20again%2C%20and%20they%20left%20him%20in%20peace.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_32%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2232%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E32%3C%2Fspan%3EThat%20very%20day%20Isaac%26%23x2019%3Bs%20servants%20came%20and%20told%20him%20about%20a%20new%20well%20they%20had%20dug.%20%26%23x201C%3BWe%26%23x2019%3Bve%20found%20water!%26%23x201D%3B%20they%20exclaimed.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_33%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2233%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E33%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Isaac%20named%20the%20well%20Shibah%20(which%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Boath%26%23x201D%3B).%20And%20to%20this%20day%20the%20town%20that%20grew%20up%20there%20is%20called%20Beersheba%20(which%20means%20%26%23x201C%3Bwell%20of%20the%20oath%26%23x201D%3B).%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_34%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2234%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E34%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20the%20age%20of%20forty%2C%20Esau%20married%20two%20Hittite%20wives%3A%20Judith%2C%20the%20daughter%20of%20Beeri%2C%20and%20Basemath%2C%20the%20daughter%20of%20Elon.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_26_35%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2226%22%20vn%3D%2235%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E35%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Esau%26%23x2019%3Bs%20wives%20made%20life%20miserable%20for%20Isaac%20and%20Rebekah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_1%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3EGenesis%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJacob%20Steals%20Esau%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Blessing%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20day%20when%20Isaac%20was%20old%20and%20turning%20blind%2C%20he%20called%20for%20Esau%2C%20his%20older%20son%2C%20and%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BMy%20son.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BYes%2C%20Father%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Esau%20replied.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_2%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BI%20am%20an%20old%20man%20now%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Isaac%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Band%20I%20don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20know%20when%20I%20may%20die.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_3%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3ETake%20your%20bow%20and%20a%20quiver%20full%20of%20arrows%2C%20and%20go%20out%20into%20the%20open%20country%20to%20hunt%20some%20wild%20game%20for%20me.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_4%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EPrepare%20my%20favorite%20dish%2C%20and%20bring%20it%20here%20for%20me%20to%20eat.%20Then%20I%20will%20pronounce%20the%20blessing%20that%20belongs%20to%20you%2C%20my%20firstborn%20son%2C%20before%20I%20die.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_5%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20Rebekah%20overheard%20what%20Isaac%20had%20said%20to%20his%20son%20Esau.%20So%20when%20Esau%20left%20to%20hunt%20for%20the%20wild%20game%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_6%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3Eshe%20said%20to%20her%20son%20Jacob%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BListen.%20I%20overheard%20your%20father%20say%20to%20Esau%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_7%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2018%3BBring%20me%20some%20wild%20game%20and%20prepare%20me%20a%20delicious%20meal.%20Then%20I%20will%20bless%20you%20in%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20presence%20before%20I%20die.%26%23x2019%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_8%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%2C%20my%20son%2C%20listen%20to%20me.%20Do%20exactly%20as%20I%20tell%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_9%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EGo%20out%20to%20the%20flocks%2C%20and%20bring%20me%20two%20fine%20young%20goats.%20I%26%23x2019%3Bll%20use%20them%20to%20prepare%20your%20father%26%23x2019%3Bs%20favorite%20dish.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_10%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20take%20the%20food%20to%20your%20father%20so%20he%20can%20eat%20it%20and%20bless%20you%20before%20he%20dies.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22gene_27_11%22%20bk%3D%22gene%22%20ch%3D%2227%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BBut%20look%2C%26%23x201D%3B%20Jacob%20replied%20to%20Rebekah%2C%20%26%23x201C%3Bmy%20brother%2C%20Esau%2C%20is%20a%20hairy%20man